    <div class="container row pt-4" id="pkg-content">
        <div class="col-8 box rounded p-3" id="readme-section">
            
                <document><h1>SDL2 for Nim</h1>
<p>This package contains the bindings for SDL2 to Nim.</p>
<h1>Pre-requisites</h1>
<p>You must install the SDL2 C libraries before these Nim bindings can be used.</p>
<h2>macOS</h2>
<h4>Homebrew</h4>
<p>If you don&apos;t already have Homebrew installed, install it from <a href="https://brew.sh/">the Homebrew site</a>.</p>
<p>Install the SDL2 C libraries:</p>
<pre>  <code class="language-bash">brew install sdl2{,_gfx,_image,_mixer,_net,_ttf}
</code></pre>
<h4>MacPorts</h4>
<p>If you don&apos;t already have Macports installed, install it from <a href="https://www.macports.org">the Macports site</a>.</p>
<pre>  <code class="language-bash">sudo port install libsdl2 libsdl2_gfx libsdl2_image libsdl2_mixer libsdl2_ttf libsdl2_net
</code></pre>
<h2>Linux</h2>
<p>Install SDL2 development libraries using your distribution&apos;s packaging tool of choice.</p>
<h2>Windows</h2>
<p>Using SDL2 with <a href="https://mingw-w64.org">mingw-w64</a> environment</p>
<ul>
<li>Install <a href="https://sourceforge.net/projects/mingw-w64/files/Toolchains%20targetting%20Win32/Personal%20Builds/mingw-builds/installer/mingw-w64-install.exe">mingw-w64-builds</a>. Check that <code>x86_64-w64-mingw32\bin\</code> from the installed mingw toolchain is in your <code>PATH</code> variable.</li>
<li>Download <a href="https://www.libsdl.org/download-2.0.php">SDL2 Development Libraries</a> for MinGW</li>
<li>Extract contents of the downloaded archive to your mingw-w64 folder (for example, <code>SDL2-2.0.12\x86_64-w64-mingw32\</code> to <code>mingw-w64\x86_64-8.1.0-posix-seh-rt_v6-rev0\mingw64\x86_64-w64-mingw32\</code>)</li>
</ul>
<h3>Static linking SDL2</h3>
<p>Pass the following options to nim on compilation:
<code>--dynlibOverride:libSDL2 --passL:&quot;-static -lmingw32 -lSDL2main -lSDL2 -mwindows  -Wl,--no-undefined -Wl,--dynamicbase -Wl,--nxcompat -Wl,--high-entropy-va -lm -ldinput8 -ldxguid -ldxerr8 -luser32 -lgdi32 -lwinmm -limm32 -lole32 -loleaut32 -lshell32 -lsetupapi -lversion -luuid&quot;</code>
Options for the linker (<code>--passL:</code>) except <code>-static</code> are taken from <code>sdl2-config.cmake</code> which is included in SDL2 Development Libraries.</p>
<h1>Installation</h1>
<p>Add <code>requires &quot;sdl2&quot;</code> to your <code>.nimble</code> file.</p>
<p>You can also install manually with <code>nimble install sdl2</code> if your project does not yet have a nimble package file.</p>
<p>For more information on using nimble, consult <a href="https://nim-lang.org/docs/lib.html#nimble">the nim documentation</a>.</p>
<h1>Documentation</h1>
<p>For documentation about SDL2 see <a href="https://wiki.libsdl.org/">wiki.libsdl.org</a>.</p>
</document>
            
